M a l e: Protarsomeres and mesotarsomeres 1 to 3 distinctly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 182, 183
) 0.84-0.87 mm long, strongly sclerotized. Median lobe with robust articular process and long, weakly inflexed apical process. Ventral branch of apical process gradually narrowed apically, curved and acute at tip in dorsal view, truncate in lateral view; dorsal branches asymmetrical. Parameres sinuate, overlapping and widened in apical sections in dorsal view, almost evenly broad up to level of tip of median lobe in lateral view. Internal sac with very dense, short, spine-like and scale-like structures and dorsal sclerotized plate.
